About
Liberace is a fascinating Las Vegas Strip origin story, involving many celebrities and personalities of note. This is the only tour of the legendary collections of influential showman Liberace, at the former residence of Michael Jackson in Las Vegas. Request an invitation to be one of the few to see the costumes, pianos, historic photos and documents, fine art and treasures, narrated by the Chairman of the Foundation himself. It's not open to the general public. See why Carlos Santana, Tyga and YG recorded "Mamacita" here in 2018. Find out how Liberace costumes became the topic of the 2019 MET Gala; hear why Cardi B borrowed the Liberace piano for her performance on the 2019 Grammys. Experience the route through this mansion, taken by Broadway and West End star Michael Ball , see why the recorded amid the Liberace collection. Learn why Boy George took this tour and recorded the song "How To Be a Chandelier" about Liberace, in 2023.
Duration: 2-3 hours

I went prepared to condescend, but came away with greater respect for Liberace
Jul 2024 • Solo
I was in Las Vegas recently, and I could think of no better way to spend a free afternoon than a visit to the Liberace Museum Collection at Thriller Villa. I live in Wisconsin, and Liberace is a local boy made good -- he grew up in West Allis, a suburb of Milwaukee.

The tour is not cheap, but they do it up right: An Uber picks you up and delivers you to the Villa, where the extensive tour is given to small groups only. In fact, the other people who booked the same tour I did had to cancel, yet the guide invited to come anyway. Ultimately, I had a private tour!

My guide, by the way, was Jonathan Warren, the Chairman of the Liberace Foundation. I don't know if he conducts all the tours, but he is trove not only of Liberace lore, but of Las Vegas history as well. He wove the history of Liberace and Vegas into the currents of popular culture of the time -- and with the broader society.

A word, too, about "Thriller Villa." The collection is housed there where Michael Jackson lived. Liberace evidently put him onto it when Jackson returned to the US after living in Bahrain for a time after his legal difficulties. To be associated two such vivid personalities gives the house its own compelling presence.

Then there's the collection. It includes a number of Liberace's pianos, his famous candelabra, all kinds of personal memorabilia, and -- of course -- many of his ever more outlandish costumes. You can only revel in the kitschy excess of it all

And yet what also comes through, particularly in Mr. Warren's narration, is that under all the glitz and tinsel is a talented performer, who through force of personality made things happen. I went to the collection with the whiff of a patronizing attitude toward Liberace, but I left with a greater respect for the man.
Written October 28, 2024

Great tour of all things Liberace at Thriller Villa
Feb 2024 • Couples
Jonathan gave my wife and I a very in-depth tour of the Liberace Collection at Thriller Villa. His passion was evident as he detailed everything from Liberace’s birth through his entire life. We learned so much over the course of 3 hours.

The collection is amazing. There is so much to see and Jonathan’s narration added to the enjoyment.
Seeing the elaborate costumes brought back many memories I have of Liberace’s flamboyance and showmanship.

In addition to Liberace, there was much knowledge shared about Liberace’s family, how he got started in Chicago and his residency in Las Vegas among so many other things.

The home is impressive. Knowing that Michael Jackson lived here as he prepared for his Vegas residency added yet another interesting element. I highly recommend this tour!

what is the price for seniors
Written December 17, 2017
jonathanwarren
Las Vegas, Nevada
5 contributions
This attraction is extremely limited as to the number of guests. Were it not for volunteers and the donation of the facility, we could not offer it to donors at this level, as the donation amount does not cover the costs. Because we already offer it for as little as possible, and because we are bound to Liberace's own instructions to discount and provide free access for students of the performing arts instead, there is no senior discount offered. Your donation serves the next generation of artists, as mandated by Liberace. We thank you in advance for understanding.
